reviews.review_text:
The Last Two for me.   This show and the night before were the only GD shows between 1992 and 1995 that I truly enjoyed.  Garcia was revived and this was the first run of shows back home in the Bay Area after yet another health scare during the summer.  Jerry's Halloween show at the Oakland Coliseum Arena six weeks prior was his first public appearance after being ill and was one of the most wonderful nights I had in my life and looked one of the best nights Garcia ever had as well.  There was some old GD magic in these two latter shows that was strangely not present during the first three nights of this five night run.  

I like this Loser, TMNS, and even S>F is pretty darn good (for the era).  A 20-minute Space?  Jeezus, that's awful.  The encore is unspeakably bad, like this two-fer always was.  I think Kevin Tobin's Matrix is by far the best overall source.  This and the GEMS sources are both very good.  

Though I never saw the Dead play as well again in their careers, Garcia shined mightily at the Warfield in JGB until the very end.
